export FLASK_APP=main.py
export FLASK_ENV=development
flask run --host=0.0.0.0 --port=8080


Added a crontab to run the server on reboot. Which makes the app run on every reboot
#Crontab -e

“ @reboot screen -dmS "flsk-running" bash -c "trap 'echo gotsigint' INT; 
cd /home/ubuntu/site ; 
pip3 install flask ; 
python -m pip install python-dotenv ; 
pip3 install wheel ; 
pip install flask-mysql ; 
pip3 install flask-mysqldb ; 
pip3 install Flask-Mail ; 
source venv/bin/activate ; e
xport FLASK_APP=main.py ; 
export FLASK_ENV=development ; 
flask run --host=0.0.0.0 --port=8080 ;  
bash"  “

#Crontab -l (to show running crontab)

The above crontab wich run on every reboot in installs and update each modules and runs the flask run command which turns up the flask web app . which is redirected by apache webserver
